other_tests.findings: Small nodule in the left lower lobe measures up to 3 mm in diameter, small calcified granuloma present at the right lung base, small hypoattenuating lesion in the sixth segment of the liver measuring up to 15 mm likely benign hemangioma, common hepatic duct dilated up to 12 mm in diameter, gall bladder mildly distended with mild irregular wall thickening, lumen filled with stones.
